  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until caramelized, about 10 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the chopped bell pepper and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the ground pork and cook, breaking it up with a spoon, until no longer pink, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the caraway seeds, paprika, salt, and black pepper, and stir to combine.",
    "Deglaze the pan with red wine vinegar and water, scraping up any browned bits from the bottom of the pan.",
    "Simmer the mixture, stirring occasionally, until the liquid has reduced and the pork is crispy and golden brown, about 10 minutes.",
    "Stir in chopped fresh parsley and serve hot."
